.xal:AddressDetails.description: This container defines the details of the address. Can define multiple addresses including tracking address history

.xal:AddressLine.description: Free format address representation. An address can have more than one line. The order of the AddressLine elements must be preserved.

.xal:AdministrativeArea.description: Examples of administrative areas are provinces counties, special regions (such as "Rijnmond"), etc.

anyOf.description: Name of the administrative area. eg. MI in USA, NSW in Australia

items.description: Name of the administrative area. eg. MI in USA, NSW in Australia

xal:SubAdministrativeArea.description:
Specification of a sub-administrative area. An example of a sub-administrative areas is a county. There are two places where the name of an administrative 
area can be specified and in this case, one becomes sub-administrative area.

anyOf.description: Name of the sub-administrative area

items.description: Name of the sub-administrative area

.xal:CountryName.description: Specification of the name of a country.

.xal:Department.description: Subdivision in the firm: School of Physics at Victoria University (School of Physics is the department)

anyOf.description: Specification of the name of a department.

items.description: Specification of the name of a department.

xal:MailStop.description: A MailStop is where the the mail is delivered to within a premise/subpremise/firm or a facility.

.xal:Locality.description: Locality is one level lower than adminisstrative area. Eg.: cities, reservations and any other built-up areas.

xal:DependentLocality.description:
Dependent localities are Districts within cities/towns, locality divisions, postal 
divisions of cities, suburbs, etc. DependentLocality is a recursive element, but no nesting deeper than two exists (Locality-DependentLocality-DependentLocality).

xal:LargeMailUser.description: Specification of a large mail user address. Examples of large mail users are postal companies, companies in France with a cedex number, hospitals and airports with their own post code. Large mail user addresses do not have a street name with premise name or premise number in countries like Netherlands. But they have a POBox and street also in countries like France

anyOf.description: Name of the locality

items.description: Name of the locality

xal:PostalRoute.description: A Postal van is specific for a route as in Is`rael, Rural route

.xal:PostBox.description: Specification of a postbox like mail delivery point. Only a single postbox number can be specified. Examples of postboxes are POBox, free mail numbers, etc.

xal:Firm.description:
Specification of a firm, company, organization, etc. It can be specified as part of an address that contains a street or a postbox. It is therefore different from 
a large mail user address, which contains no street.

xal:PostBoxNumber.description: Specification of the number of a postbox

xal:PostBoxNumberExtension.description: Some countries like USA have POBox as 12345-123

xal:PostBoxNumberPrefix.description: Specification of the prefix of the post box number. eg. A in POBox:A-123

xal:PostBoxNumberSuffix.description: Specification of the suffix of the post box number. eg. A in POBox:123A

.xal:PostOffice.description: Specification of a post office. Examples are a rural post office where post is delivered and a post office containing post office boxes.

anyOf.description: Specification of the name of the post office. This can be a rural postoffice where post is delivered or a post office containing post office boxes.

items.description: Specification of the name of the post office. This can be a rural postoffice where post is delivered or a post office containing post office boxes.

xal:PostOfficeNumber.description: Specification of the number of the postoffice. Common in rural postoffices

xal:PostalRoute.description: A Postal van is specific for a route as in Is`rael, Rural route

.xal:PostalCode.description: PostalCode is the container element for either simple or complex (extended) postal codes. Type: Area Code, Postcode, etc.

xal:PostTown.description: A post town is not the same as a locality. A post town can encompass a collection of (small) localities. It can also be a subpart of a locality. An actual post town in Norway is "Bergen".

anyOf.description: Name of the post town

items.description: Name of the post town

xal:PostTownSuffix.description: GENERAL PO in MIAMI GENERAL PO

anyOf.description: Specification of a postcode. The postcode is formatted according to country-specific rules. Example: SW3 0A8-1A, 600074, 2067

items.description: Specification of a postcode. The postcode is formatted according to country-specific rules. Example: SW3 0A8-1A, 600074, 2067

anyOf.description: Examples are: 1234 (USA), 1G (UK), etc.

items.description: Examples are: 1234 (USA), 1G (UK), etc.

.xal:Premise.description:
Specification of a single premise, for example a house or a building. The premise as a whole has a unique premise (house) number or a premise name.  There could be more than 
one premise in a street referenced in an address. For example a building address near a major shopping centre or raiwlay station

anyOf.description: Specification of the name of a building.

items.description: Specification of the name of a building.

xal:Firm.description: Specification of a firm, company, organization, etc. It can be specified as part of an address that contains a street or a postbox. It is therefore different from a large mail user address, which contains no street.

xal:MailStop.description: A MailStop is where the the mail is delivered to within a premise/subpremise/firm or a facility.

anyOf.description: Specification of the name of the premise (house, building, park, farm, etc). A premise name is specified when the premise cannot be addressed using a street name plus premise (house) number.

items.description: Specification of the name of the premise (house, building, park, farm, etc). A premise name is specified when the premise cannot be addressed using a street name plus premise (house) number.

xal:PremiseNumberRange.description: Specification for defining the premise number range. Some premises have number as Building C1-C7

xal:PremiseNumberRangeFrom.description: Start number details of the premise number range

xal:PremiseNumberRangeTo.description: End number details of the premise number range

anyOf.description: Specification of a single sub-premise. Examples of sub-premises are apartments and suites. Each sub-premise should be uniquely identifiable.

items.description: Specification of a single sub-premise. Examples of sub-premises are apartments and suites. Each sub-premise should be uniquely identifiable.

.xal:PremiseNumber.description: Specification of the identifier of the premise (house, building, etc). Premises in a street are often uniquely identified by means of consecutive identifiers. The identifier can be a number, a letter or any combination of the two.

.xal:Thoroughfare.description:
Specification of a thoroughfare. A thoroughfare could be a rd, street, canal, river, etc.  Note dependentlocality in a street. For example, in some countries, a large street will 
have many subdivisions with numbers. Normally the subdivision name is the same as the road name, but with a number to identifiy it. Eg. SOI SUKUMVIT 3, SUKUMVIT RD, BANGKOK

xal:DependentLocality.description:
Dependent localities are Districts within cities/towns, locality divisions, postal 
divisions of cities, suburbs, etc. DependentLocality is a recursive element, but no nesting deeper than two exists (Locality-DependentLocality-DependentLocality).

xal:DependentThoroughfare.description: DependentThroughfare is related to a street; occurs in GB, IE, ES, PT

xal:ThoroughfareLeadingType.description: Appears before the thoroughfare name. Ed. Spanish: Avenida Aurora, where Avenida is the leading type / French: Rue Moliere, where Rue is the leading type.

anyOf.description: Specification of the name of a Thoroughfare (also dependant street name): street name, canal name, etc.

items.description: Specification of the name of a Thoroughfare (also dependant street name): street name, canal name, etc.

xal:ThoroughfarePostDirection.description: 221-bis Baker Street North, where North is the post-direction. The post-direction appears after the name.

xal:ThoroughfarePreDirection.description: North Baker Street, where North is the pre-direction. The direction appears before the name.

xal:ThoroughfareTrailingType.description: Appears after the thoroughfare name. Ed. British: Baker Lane, where Lane is the trailing type.

xal:Firm.description:
Specification of a firm, company, organization, etc. It can be specified as part of an address that contains a street or a postbox. It is therefore different from 
a large mail user address, which contains no street.

xal:ThoroughfareLeadingType.description: Appears before the thoroughfare name. Ed. Spanish: Avenida Aurora, where Avenida is the leading type / French: Rue Moliere, where Rue is the leading type.

anyOf.description: Specification of the name of a Thoroughfare (also dependant street name): street name, canal name, etc.

items.description: Specification of the name of a Thoroughfare (also dependant street name): street name, canal name, etc.

anyOf.description: A container to represent a range of numbers (from x thru y)for a thoroughfare. eg. 1-2 Albert Av

items.description: A container to represent a range of numbers (from x thru y)for a thoroughfare. eg. 1-2 Albert Av

xal:ThoroughfarePostDirection.description: 221-bis Baker Street North, where North is the post-direction. The post-direction appears after the name.

xal:ThoroughfarePreDirection.description: North Baker Street, where North is the pre-direction. The direction appears before the name.

xal:ThoroughfareTrailingType.description: Appears after the thoroughfare name. Ed. British: Baker Lane, where Lane is the trailing type.

.xal:ThoroughfareNumber.description: Eg.: 23 Archer street or 25/15 Zero Avenue, etc

.xal:ThoroughfareNumberPrefix.description: Prefix before the number. A in A12 Archer Street

.xal:ThoroughfareNumberSuffix.description: Suffix after the number. A in 12A Archer Street

.xal:xAL.description: Root element for a list of addresses

anyOf.description: A country code according to the specified scheme

items.description: A country code according to the specified scheme

xal:PostalServiceElements.description: Postal authorities use specific postal service data to expedient delivery of mail

anyOf.description: A unique identifier of an address assigned by postal authorities. Example: DPID in Australia

xal:AddressLatitudeDirection.description: Latitude direction of delivery address;N = North and S = South

xal:AddressLongitudeDirection.description: Longtitude direction of delivery address;N=North and S=South

xal:SortingCode.description: Used for sorting addresses. Values may for example be CEDEX 16 (France)

anyOf.description: any postal service elements not covered by the container can be represented using this element

items.description: any postal service elements not covered by the container can be represented using this element

Dependent localities are Districts within cities/towns, locality divisions, postal 
divisions of cities, suburbs, etc. DependentLocality is a recursive element, but no nesting deeper than two exists (Locality-DependentLocality-DependentLocality).

items.description: Name of the dependent locality

xal:DependentLocalityNumber.description: Number of the dependent locality. Some areas are numbered. Eg. SECTOR 5 in a Suburb as in India or SOI SUKUMVIT 10 as in Thailand

Examples of large mail users are postal companies, companies in France with a cedex number, hospitals and airports with their own post code. Large mail user addresses do not have a street name with premise name or premise number in countries like Netherlands. But they have a POBox and street also in countries like France

xal:LargeMailUserIdentifier.description: Specification of the identification number of a large mail user. An example are the Cedex codes in France.

anyOf.description: Name of the large mail user. eg. Smith Ford International airport

items.description: Name of the large mail user. eg. Smith Ford International airport

xal:MailStopName.description: Name of the the Mail Stop. eg. MSP, MS, etc

xal:MailStopNumber.description: Number of the Mail stop. eg. 123 in MS 123

xal:SubPremise.description:
Specification of a single sub-premise. Examples of sub-premises are apartments and suites. 
Each sub-premise should be uniquely identifiable. SubPremiseType: Specification of the name of a sub-premise type. Possible values not limited to: Suite, Appartment, Floor, Unknown
Multiple levels within a premise by recursively calling SubPremise Eg. Level 4, Suite 2, Block C

xal:SubPremiseLocation.description: Name of the SubPremise Location. eg. LOBBY, BASEMENT, GROUND FLOOR, etc...

anyOf.description: Name of the SubPremise

items.description: Name of the SubPremise

anyOf.description:
Specification of the identifier of a sub-premise. Examples of sub-premises are apartments and suites. sub-premises in a building are often uniquely identified by means of consecutive
identifiers. The identifier can be a number, a letter or any combination of the two. In the latter case, the identifier includes exactly one variable (range) part, which is either a 
number or a single letter that is surrounded by fixed parts at the left (prefix) or the right (postfix).

items.description:
Specification of the identifier of a sub-premise. Examples of sub-premises are apartments and suites. sub-premises in a building are often uniquely identified by means of consecutive
identifiers. The identifier can be a number, a letter or any combination of the two. In the latter case, the identifier includes exactly one variable (range) part, which is either a 
number or a single letter that is surrounded by fixed parts at the left (prefix) or the right (postfix).

anyOf.description: Prefix of the sub premise number. eg. A in A-12

items.description: Prefix of the sub premise number. eg. A in A-12

anyOf.description: Suffix of the sub premise number. eg. A in 12A

items.description: Suffix of the sub premise number. eg. A in 12A
